<pdd-reason>Provides a persistent SSE stream for real-time audit progress updates with heartbeats.</pdd-reason>

You are implementing `app/api/pipeline/audit/stream/route.ts`, an SSE (Server-Sent Events) endpoint for real-time audit progress updates in a video production pipeline.

Role & Scope
This endpoint provides a persistent connection for the client to listen for audit events. While the audit job itself is driven by a separate POST request, this stream ensures the connection remains active and can receive broadcasted updates.

Requirements
1. `GET /api/pipeline/audit/stream` — returns an SSE stream.
2. Initial event: Sends `data: {"type":"connected"}\n\n` immediately upon connection.
3. Heartbeat: Sends `data: {"type":"heartbeat"}\n\n` every 15 seconds to prevent connection timeouts.
4. Connection Management: 
   - Monitors `request.signal` for client disconnection.
   - Clears the heartbeat interval and closes the controller on disconnect.
5. Error Handling: Uses try-catch when enqueuing heartbeat events to handle already-closed streams gracefully.
6. Headers:
   - `Content-Type: text/event-stream`
   - `Cache-Control: no-cache`
   - `Connection: keep-alive`

Dependencies
None.

Instructions
- Use the Next.js App Router `GET` handler.
- Implement the stream using `new ReadableStream` with a `start(controller)` callback.
- Use `TextEncoder` for encoding JSON strings into `Uint8Array` for the stream.
- Ensure all resources (intervals) are cleaned up in the `request.signal` "abort" listener.

Deliverable
- `app/api/pipeline/audit/stream/route.ts` — SSE endpoint with initial connection and 15s heartbeat.

